# Decisions Addendum 004 — Benchmark Source System

## Decision 023: Replace Pack-First Thinking With Source-First Thinking

Decision:
- The earlier benchmark pack system is incomplete/flawed if treated as the user-facing source of benchmark data.
- Aim Brain should use a benchmark source system.

Correct model:

```text
External benchmark source
↓
Source adapter
↓
Normalized benchmark definition
↓
Validation
↓
Installed local definition
↓
Aim Brain Engine
```

Status:
- locked

---

## Decision 024: Benchmark Definitions Should Come From Normal Sources

Decision:
- Aim Brain should support benchmark definitions from common external formats/sources:
  - built-in curated data
  - local JSON
  - local CSV
  - GitHub raw JSON/CSV later
  - public Google Sheet CSV later
  - custom-created definitions later

Reason:
- Benchmarks already exist in external communities and tools.
- Aim Brain should not force everything to originate as an Aim Brain-specific pack.

Status:
- locked

